    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i'll get some sulfur then. but i'm still a bit worried about the nutrients just... disappearing or being stripped away from the soil so fast. is there anything else that could be stealing the goodness from the plants?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you're concerned about nutrients being depleted too quickly, there are a few things to consider. First, make sure that your watering practices aren't causing the issue. Overwatering can lead to nutrient leaching, where nutrients are washed away from the soil and out of reach of your plants. Also, check for soil compaction, which can impede root growth and nutrient uptake. Lastly, consider introducing beneficial organisms like earthworms, which can help improve soil structure and nutrient availability. If you're still worried, you could also apply a slow-release fertilizer to provide a steady supply of nutrients over time.",
      "source": "target",
